<h2>Alternate target</h2>
<p>By default a tooltip will be triggered by interaction with the dom node it wraps. To define an alternate dom node, use the <code>target</code> attribute. This allows more flexibility in markup.</p>
<div class="bs-docs-example tooltip-demo">
    <div class="bs-docs-tooltip-examples">
        <button id="findOutMore" class="btn">Find out more <i class="icon-question-sign"></i></button>
        <tooltip target="findOutMore" title="Here's some more info"></tooltip>
    </div>
</div>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">
{% set tooltipExample5 %}
<button id="findOutMore" class="btn">Find out more <i class="icon-question-sign"></i></button>
<!-- other markup here -->
<tooltip target="findOutMore" title="Here's some more info"></tooltip>{% endset %}{{tooltipExample5|e}}
</pre>

